sec.p:
The enchytraeid fauna is diverse and abundant in the Korean forests, but intensive studies have started only recently, which resulted in the description of two new genera and 26 new species to date ( Dózsa-Farkas & Hong 2010 ; Christensen & Dózsa-Farkas 2012 ; Dózsa-Farkas et al. 2015; Hong & Dózsa-Farkas 2018 ; Dózsa-Farkas et al . 2018, 2019a,b;
Nagy et al. 2020
,
Felföldi et al . 2020
). In this paper, further four species new to science and from three different genera are presented from Jeoksangsan (Mt Jeoksang, located in Deogyusan National Park, Jeollabuk-do province ), located in the central part of Korea (
.). There are two earlier reports of the enchytraeid fauna from the Deogyusan National Park, but from Deogyusan: one species new to science, Cognettia koreana Felföldi et al ., 2020
, and one species, Bryodrilus ehlersi Ude, 1892
, as a new record in Korea (
Nagy et al . 2020
).

Methods of molecular analysis . Genomic DNA was isolated with the DNeasy Blood & Tissue Kit (Qiagen) according to the instructions given by the manufacturer. CO1 and H3 genes and the ITS region were amplified separately by PCR using the primer pairs HCO2198 (5’ -TAA ACT TCA GGG TGA CCA AAA AAT CA- 3’) and LCO1490 (5’ -GGT CAA CAA ATC ATA AAG ATA TTG G- 3’) (
Folmer et al . 1994
), H3a-F (5’ -ATG GCT CGT ACC AAG CAG ACV GC-3’) and H3a-R (5’-ATA TCC TTR GGC ATR ATR GTG AC-3’) (
Colgan et al . 1998
), ETTS1 (5’ -TGC TTA AGT TCA GCG GGT- 3’) and ETTS2 (5’ -TAA CAA GGT TTC CGT AGG TGA A- 3’) ( Kane

